description: From Middle English famous, from Anglo-Norman famous, from Latin fāmōsus. Displaced native Old English hlīsful.

adjectives.description: famous (comparative more famous, superlative most famous)

examples: Some people are only famous within their city.

verbs.description: famous (third-person singular simple present famouses, present participle famousing, simple past and past participle famoused)

entries.meaning: (transitive, obsolete) To make famous; to bring renown to.
